         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">With a resounding, (lovely brahmasvara-voice) surpassing the divine drums (he [the Buddha Śākyamuni] called the noble Maitreya.)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #a7 #a8 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6 #b7 #b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1997"/></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... superior, excellent for the benefit of many. The one who ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... as if a single atom is measured up against the Sumeru mountain ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Remember, o Maitreya, that we for asamkhyeyas and</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>15 n.1</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">kalpas ... we have been cherishing the wish (of obtaining Buddhahood). My wish for Buddhahood (has been fulfilled). ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">I obtained the Buddhahood and made turn the wheel of the Law. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">I have made seen miracles (to the heretics.) At the occasion of the customary gift of food in the summer ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... from (father) and mother. I have established well-being for them. (I taught them) the four truths.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the four truths. I have evoked [in them] a thinking without confusion towards Buddhahood.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... while the life of the beings [lasts] 120 years, I have now completely performed this task without fault.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... while the life of beings [lasts] 80,000 years, you will be tathāgata with the name Maitreya. In</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>59</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>15, 237</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">that way ... you will make manifest the road towards nirvāna. As I now have made ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">You will make manifest the road [towards the nirvāṇa].</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>625</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... den ... Weg (mach)ten wir offenbar.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... the ... path we (ma)de evident.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>349</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... You certainly, o Maitreya, you (will lead) disciples by countless thousands.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>334</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... from the  Buddha (Ratnaśikhin) onwards until the Buddha Kāśyapa, by ten thousands ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>233</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the idea (will come to me) that redeems the beings which have not been redeemed by the previous Buddhas.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">O noble one, remember the resolution made by yourself in the past!</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels">MaitrHami 4, 11b 21-12b 24</note><note type="philcomment">This fragment contains part of the fourth act of the Maitreyasamitināṭaka; an Uy. parallel is MaitrHami 4, 11b21-ca. 12b27. See also <bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1999"/><citedRange>197-8</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">Fragment of a manuscript which includes A 251 - A 294 (cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:gengetal2004a"/><citedRange>64-65</citedRange></bibl>).</note></p>
